  "prompt": "How does flitto app make money?",
  "response": "Flitto, a language translation app, primarily makes money through several revenue streams:\n\n1. **Translation Services:** Users can request translations for various types of content, including text, images, and voice recordings. Flitto charges a fee for these translation services, which varies based on the complexity and urgency of the request.\n\n2. **Crowdsourced Translations:** Flitto utilizes a network of freelance translators who work on translation requests posted by users. The app takes a commission from the payments made to these freelancers.\n\n3. **Corporate Services:** Flitto offers translation services to businesses and organizations. These clients often require translation for documents, websites, apps, and other professional content, providing a steady source of revenue.\n\n4. **Advertising:** The app includes advertising in its free version, generating revenue from the ad impressions and click-throughs.\n\n5. **Premium Subscriptions:** Flitto might offer premium subscription plans for users who want access to advanced features, faster response times, or higher priority in the translation queue.\n\n6. **Data Sales:** Flitto collects valuable linguistic data through its translation activities, which can be monetized by selling to companies that need large datasets for machine learning, AI training, or other linguistic research purposes.\n\nThese diversified revenue streams allow Flitto to sustain its operations and make a profit while providing language translation services across the globe.",
